      <h1 class='title'>Chemical Weapons Act</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 June 2004 vol 662 cc38-9WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_39ws' title='Col. 39WS &mdash; HL Deb 17 June 2004 vol 662 c39WS' name='column_39ws' href='#column_39ws' rel='bookmark'>39WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0662P0-07181'>
        <a name='S5LV0662P0_20040617_LWS_7'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-sainsbury' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0662P0_20040617_LWS_7' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Sainsbury' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-david-sainsbury" title="Mr David Sainsbury">Lord Sainsbury of Turville</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0662P0-07181">My honourable friend the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Trade and Industry (Nigel Griffiths) has made the following Written Statement.</p><p id="S5LV0662P0-07182">I am pleased to announce that in accordance with the requirements of the <a href="/acts/chemical-weapons-act-1996">Chemical Weapons Act 1996</a>, I have today laid a report before the House on its operation during 2003.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
